https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/pul:
ClientPermissionsV2.hasPermission(ClientModel, scope) can throw NullPointerException when the per-client resource is missing and the fallback resource-type resource is also missing. In hasPermission(ClientModel,...):
- resource = resourceStore.findByName(server, client.getId(), server.getId());
- if (resource == null) { resource = AdminPermissionsSchema.SCHEMA.getResourceTypeResource(...); if (policyStore.findByResource(server, resource).isEmpty()) return false; }
If getResourceTypeResource(...) returns null, policyStore.findByResource(server, resource) dereferences null (and later ResourcePermission(resource, ...) would as well).

AuthzClientCryptoProvider.getBouncyCastleProvider() returns the provider of the default KeyStore instance, not a BouncyCastle provider. This is a wrong provider mapping given the method name/contract.
Evidence (diff):
